# Accessibility (A11y) Standards

Author: rules/merge
Version: 1.1.0

## Context

- Enforces WCAG-oriented checks and best practices across components and markup
- Applies to interactions, visual elements, structure, and assistive technology support

<rule>
name: accessibility_standards
description: Enforce accessibility standards and WCAG compliance
filters:
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\.(vue|jsx|tsx|html|php|css|scss|sass)$"

actions:
  - type: enforce
    conditions:
      - pattern: "<img[^>]+(?!alt=)[^>]*>"
        message: "Images must include meaningful alt attributes."

      - pattern: "aria-[a-z]+=\"\""
        message: "ARIA attributes should not be empty; provide meaningful values."

      - pattern: "<button[^>]*>(?![^<]*[^\\s])[^<]*</button>"
        message: "Buttons should have descriptive content (or aria-label)."

      - pattern: "<a[^>]*href=\"#[^\"]*\"[^>]*>(?![^<]*<svg)[^<]*</a>"
        message: "Links with href='#' need descriptive context via aria-label or proper target."

      - pattern: "<input[^>]+type=\"(text|email|password|search|tel|url)\"[^>]*>"
        pattern_negate: "aria-label|aria-labelledby|title|<label"
        message: "Textual inputs must have associated labels or ARIA labelling."

      - pattern: "<video[^>]*>(?!<track)[^<]*</video>"
        message: "Videos should include captions via <track>."

  - type: suggest
    message: |
      **Accessibility Best Practices:**
      - **Heading hierarchy:** Use h1–h6 in logical order.
      - **Keyboard navigation:** Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible with visible focus.
      - **Semantic HTML:** Prefer `nav`, `article`, `section`, `aside` for structure.
      - **Color contrast:** Meet WCAG ratios (4.5:1 normal, 3:1 large text).
      - **Skip links:** Provide “skip to main content”.
      - **Focus management:** Manage focus for modals/dynamic content.
      - **Form labels:** Associate labels with controls or use ARIA.
      - **Descriptive links:** Avoid generic “click here”.
      - **Touch targets:** Minimum ~44x44px on mobile.
      - **html lang:** Set primary language.

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.1
</rule>

## Examples

Example (valid):

```html
<!-- Properly labeled input with helper text -->
<label for="email">Email</label>
<input type="email" id="email" aria-describedby="email-helper" />
<p id="email-helper">We'll never share your email address.</p>
```

Example (invalid):

```html
<!-- Missing label and no ARIA attributes -->
<input type="text" />
```

